 pen &amp; paper RP game you know that grouping is a big part of it. <br>So there is a pretty good chance that the average person who starts EQ, would have an idea that it's a fantasy roleplaying game, where you get to build your character, level it up and most likely have to group with poeple. If you don't like the way the game plays, then you move onto something else. You have the option to solo for the first 60 levels, then group or you have the option to group from level 1. Sony is a business, they will try and cater for the mass player base, not the individual. <br>I have a few problems with the game, but they are things I can live with and I still enjoy EQ. If I thing a problem needs fixing, I do a feedback/ bug report.<blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Mobs shouldnt be able to summon unless they are magicians or some really uber mob. I think all mobs should give some exp no matter what level you are.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> You do relise that your average Mob IA is pretty basic, right? They can't think like a human player, they don't have the same advantage of thought, that we do. Which is why Mobs are tougher, have more HPs, can summon, can cast a spell, even though 6 people are beating on it.<br>If the Mobs had to live by the &quot;player rules&quot; then they would get slaughtered. IF you do want them to be the same as us, then give them the same equipment, resists and intelligences as us. Make it so they can think like we do... <i>&quot;Hey Blog, keel da Cleric 'un da Enchanter first. Ignore da Warrior, himz will die fast after all da casters 'ave gone splatt.&quot;</i><br>Would make the game a lot harder and challenging, but would probably make a lot of people quit, because the mobs would be tougher, than they are now.<br>Addressing &quot;Mobs should give xp at all levels&quot;... please, don't even think that. There's enough KSing in Paludal as it is, on a weekend, we don't need a few lvl 70 in there, clearing the whole zone. Sorry but it's a silly idea. <blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Another thing is quit giving us abilitys then nerfing them. You have gained a very bad rep for this.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> Best thing they did was nerf KEI and such. Yes it was fun while it lasted, but KEI, especially at lower levels made the game very unbalanced and honestly, you don't realy need KEI before lvl 45. The clarity line of spells will work for you just fine, just learn to manage your mana.<br>I can't realy think of a nerf in the last year, that has effected my game play? I still play my Monk (44) just fine and he still gets groups. Bards... well they don't seem to be happy about the AOE kiting nerf, but hey, it was good while it lasted and being able to kite half a zone is fun, all though dangerous and repiring some skill, was just a little over-balanced.<blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Which makes folks think when given a choice like we have now between a game you have written and another game &quot;Why would I play a new game written by the same company so they can treat me like they have already all over again&quot;.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Have you realy been treated badly? Have you? What have they done that would be considered &quot;Treating you badly?&quot;<br>If you mean customer service, then maybe you could be right. I am happy with their CS. I've had nothing but good CS over the last 4 years of EQ. Not that I use it often, but I find keeping my /petitions short, polite and too the point normally gets them answered within a few hours, never longer than 24 hours. With the player base Sony has to deal with and the amount of /petitions, bug reports and the rest of it, I think a few hours to 24 hours is pretty good.<br>Twice I have had problems with my billing and not being able to log into the game. Advice: Ring them, don't e-mail, don't live chat. Call them on the phone. Works like a charm every time.<br><br>And I'm going to give you a rate-up, because you sound like a Sock... and Socks need luv 2!<br><br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sun Jan  9 13:37:28 2005 by lagduff</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><b>Whiptail</b> - 62 Iksar Beastlord.<br><br><a href="HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=179974" target="akztarg">The Beer Fridge...</a><i>(Journal)</i> <br><br><i>"<b><span style='color: Red;'>The Asylum</span style='color: Red;'></b>: Only your Sock Puppets will hear you scream!"</i></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from inside my beer fridge... QLD, Australia.</td></tr></table>
